## Code Documentation Rules

### Every Function Must Have:
- JSDoc comment explaining purpose
- @param tags for all parameters with types
- @returns tag with return type
- @example if complex

### Every Component Must Have:
- Comment at top explaining purpose
- Props interface with descriptions
- Inline comments for complex logic

### When Writing Code:
1. Add JSDoc to every function
2. Add inline comments for complex logic
3. Update README.md when adding features
4. Use descriptive variable names
5. Add @example tags for non-obvious functions

### Git Commits:
Use conventional commit format:
- feat: new feature
- fix: bug fix
- docs: documentation
- refactor: code improvement

